Well - other than you see the Band of Hope and of course we went in then you see we were - as I told you then I was playing an instrument and then we - what I mean, went in to play - joined orchestra then. And we had a place in Maesteg th
en to - in this orchestra and I was the first violin. And they was having musical festivals. Gymanfa Ganu in Elsh. With every church from top end of the valley, and of course we were then - going to play there, and - it was a day out, we played in every c
hurch right through the valley. And there's such men as Doctor David Evans, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cardiff{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - Caradog Roberts. And it was a wonderful - well of course - my time was spent there.
