Well - during the summer yes we would but I mean - during the time now take for instance - harvest time. I mean now harvest
 - and when the harvest festival had been in the church in the Anglican church, all us boys in Llan then used to go round the farms - to get - a sheaf of courn, in order to decorate the church in the time you know. And of course around these farms then th
e
y had little orchards, pears - and I used to try and watch where the pears were. And we'd come back - that was the - not the sheaf of corn, not the love of fetching it, but in order to het a pocket full of pears, then one of the other boys would have some
 apples and so forth.
